headline: CEO at Rejuvall
summary:
Rayvon Reynolds is a serial entrepreneur. She's presently spearheading the continued development of a growing triumvirate of healthcare enterprises (Exo Biomedical / Rejuvall / Morganstern Urology) located in Atlanta, GA that launched in 2015.

Previously, Miss Reynolds co-founded a consumer packaged goods enterprise (DRY, Inc.) and distributor of the Woolite Drycleaner’s Secret brand of at-home cleaning kits. She holds eleven patents relating to the process of cleaning “dry clean only” clothes in the home. DRY, Inc. was sold to Summit Brands in March 2012. 

Prior to launching DRY, Miss Reynolds started and built Presstine Cleaners of Atlanta, GA into one of the single highest volume retail drycleaning stores in the US. 

Before that, Miss Reynolds was president of Moby Dick Seafood Restaurants national company. Moby Dick was the nation’s fourth largest fast-seafood chain at that time. 

Miss Reynolds is an investor in commercial real estate partnerships with an affinity for high quality single tenant sites.

Her personal passions include art, antiques, fashion. and performing magic shows.

I co-founded WheelChariot, a review platform committed to improving accessibility for the disability community. Our mission is to ensure every business is accountable and inclusive, empowering individuals with disabilities to share their experiences and rate businesses based on their accessibility.

In addition to my role at WheelChariot, I serve as the Director of Marketing at TeamWRX Staffing. Here, I apply my team-oriented approach to provide staffing solutions across Atlanta, Savannah, and Dallas-Fort Worth. My dedication to building strong teams helps businesses find the talent they need to grow and thrive.

My journey began at the Georgia Institute of Technology, where I received my Bachelor of Science in Business Administration with a concentration in Marketing. It was here that my love for storytelling and community involvement truly blossomed. I proudly served as an Executive for the Buzz Studios Film Club for two years, with my final year as President. This experience not only honed my leadership skills but also deepened my passion for creating impactful narratives.

Today, I continue to leverage my skills in marketing and storytelling to drive change, promote inclusivity, and create meaningful connections in all that I do.

headline: CEO, President & Director at Alimera Sciences
summary:
Rick joined Alimera Sciences in 2005 as CFO and assumed the position of COO in 2010. He is responsible for strategic finance, accounting, distribution logistics, human resources and  information technology. Rick brings a wealth of financial and operational management experience with both public and private ventures to the team. Since joining Alimera, he completed three rounds of venture funding totaling approximately $67 million.  In 2010 Rick led Alimera's successful IPO, raising $72 million, and negotiated a $32.5 million credit facility leading to recognition of Alimera as the "Strategic Deal of the Year" by both Southeastern BIO and Georgia BIO. 

Rick currently serves as the chairman of the board of directors and audit committee of Jones Soda Co., a Seattle-based publicly traded company, and vice-chairman of the North Metro Miracle League, an Atlanta-based charitable organization.  

Rick has been active in Atlanta business for more than 20 years, with experience that includes financial and accounting management, mergers and acquisitions, and initial public offerings, as well as entrepreneurial and start-up operational activities. Rick is the founder of two consulting practices, Brand Ignition Group and Black River Holdings, Inc. He is also the former chief financial officer and senior executive vice president of Netzee, Inc., a provider of internet banking solutions to community banks that went public in 1999. Rick started his career in Arthur Andersen’s audit and business advisory practice where he was a senior manager and a certified public accountant. He has an accounting degree from Wake Forest University.

headline: Marketing Director at Hallboys Holdings
summary:
“If it’s both terrifying and amazing then you should definitely pursue it.”
It was in high school that I read this quote, and decided I was never going to let fear rule my life. I was 18 years old when I decided to move from Georgia to Hawaii to attend the University of Hawaii. I stepped foot onto the island not knowing a soul or anything about the place. You could definitely say it was a culture shock... However, rather than feeling overwhelmed, I was very intrigued by the different people that surrounded me. 

Within a year of attending the University, I had met and befriend people from all over the world who taught me how to understand and accept one another’s differences. Through exploring the island with all different kinds of people, I learned that in order to be successful, you have to jump. Meeting and communicating with friends, colleagues, and tourist made me realize I never want to be complacent with my life or talents. Each day is a new opportunity to be a better version of yourself than you were yesterday. It is for those reasons, I decided to move to New York City after graduation to compete and learn from some of the most talented people in the world. 

I quickly realized that I had a desire to apart of a team with a more creative work environment. I accepted a job with The Beam Team in 2017 and established strengths in budgeting, time management, and strategy planning. Finding a creative solution to a problem thrills me, and working with a team to build legendary brands is both terrifying yet exhilarating.

summary:
As the Executive Director and Co-Founder of the 5G Healthcare Collaborative, I am passionate about providing a real-world environment for the digital transformation of the healthcare sector. With more than two decades of experience in creating and leading innovative ventures, I have a proven track record of delivering technical solutions and business services for startups to Fortune 100 companies.

Core competencies include new market creation, global business development, key account management, strategic alliance development, solution sales, and complex emerging technology evangelism. I have a strong background in systems integration, cloud computing, SaaS, and PaaS, as well as expertise in the latest IoT and web advances. I was a pioneer in Internet media and a serial entrepreneur with full-lifecycle custom product development skills. My mission is to foster direct connections between healthcare executives and technology providers and to showcase a wide range of emerging technologies, techniques, applications, and business processes for healthcare stakeholders at every level of the continuum of care.
position_description_1:
The 5G Healthcare Collaborative is a unique venture – designed to provide a real-world environment for the digital transformation of the Healthcare sector. From the classroom to the operating room, from the drawing board to the marketplace — the Collaborative enables members to showcase a wide range of emerging technologies, techniques, applications, and business processes for Healthcare stakeholders at every level of the Continuum of Care.

The mission of the 5G Healthcare Collaborative is crystal clear: we're building a sanctuary free from the relentless drumbeat of sales pitches and vendor-selection pressure. Here, we foster direct connections between healthcare executives grappling with IT and wireless communication challenges and the brilliant minds of engineers and systems architects from the foremost network and wireless technology giants worldwide.

Together, we sculpt, shape, and breathe life into healthcare-specific solutions that address the pressing challenges head-on. Our aim? To enable those in need to collaborate directly with the finest problem-solvers in the industry.

We're all too familiar with the interminable maze that conventional marketing and sales processes can create. But at 5G Healthcare Collaborative, we cut through the noise and propel you straight into the heart of solution development mode. Join us in this journey towards innovative healthcare solutions and streamlined progress.
position_description_2:
ENTERPRISE MOBILE/WEB LOCATION PLATFORM
Whether its improving indoor/outdoor navigation for campus visitors, using precise location sharing for mobile safety and security alerts, reducing precious time spent tracking assets throughout your campus, or ensuring privacy with encrypted text, video and file exchange... Locate Solutions delivers integrated applications to make it all happen.

INTEGRATION
Locate Solutions' applications can seamlessly interface with enterprise platforms, office productivity software, building and resource management applications and more. Adding our positioning and tracking functionalities with corresponding data will significantly improve the value of your systems' analytics.

MANAGEMENT and MAINTENANCE
Locate Solutions' applications are delivered in the form of a fully managed and maintained platform. This Platform-as-a Service model enables rapid and non-intrusive deployment, maximizes operation effectiveness and up-time and eliminates the need to place additional burden upon existing network infrastructure and IT personnel.  There is also a reduction in up-front capital costs.

SCALABILITY
Locate Solutions' applications have been specifically designed to to leverage the functionality of interchangeable modules that can be combined and integrated to fit a customers' immediate needs quickly and cost-effectively. As requirements and corresponding budgets change, additional modules and their powerful benefits can be quickly and seamlessly added to the core application  

USABILITY
Locate Solutions applications and their components are built to ensure usability, we call it N3... No Nerds Necessary!™  This simply means that those who NEED to use the applications CAN use them. Whether its administrators, marketers, security, parking control personnel, and especially your end users... both the front and back ends are built with intuitive logic to ensure usability.
position_description_3: Designed, developed, and completed an information delivery system that consolidates the "power technologies" of the Web into a single, simple application so easy to use that executives, managers, personnel, prospects, and customers can instantaneously leverage the power of those technologies through the simplistic N3 Interface™ (No Nerds Necessary). The application, iTTER8™, incorporates and leverages most of the web-based technologies that businesses need to communicate, train, market, and sell more effectively and less expensively. The most recent "iteration" of the solution includes streaming audio and video, eLearning, email, chat, Facebook & Twitter, community building & CRM, file sharing, and instant messaging combined with company-specific functions to create an all-inclusive corporate communications portal for internal and external utilization.

Projects included print, video, Internet media, education & training, national & international meetings and conferences, and broadcast advertising. My superpower is to combine visionary financial strategies with engaging human capital leadership strategies. I coach executives to successfully navigate complex changes, drive organizational transformation, scale businesses effectively, and make significant advances in their careers.

headline: CEO at Knightworks, LLC
summary:
Laura L. Knight received her undergraduate and master’s degrees from the Georgia Institute of Technology in Business and Environmental Public Policy respectively. She completed her doctorate at the University of Georgia in Geography with a specialization in Marine Science and GIS/Remote Sensing. 

Her research interests include water quality management and policy through quantitative measurement of habitat disruption and species mortality potentially linked to regional disasters and climate change.  She has actively engaged in project management and environmental assessments that have included everything from tagging/monitoring marine life off the coast of Georgia and South Carolina to providing consulting sevices for streamlining data management in the fields of engineering, healthcare and multimedia communications. 

Dr. Knight’s prior research investigated the water quality and habitat of the endangered shortnose sturgeon in the Savannah River.  Her research used both qualitative and quantitative methods by employing mid-range frequency side-scan and high frequency DIDSON SONAR to examine the uniqueness of specific habitat features. Her projects have contributed to the refinement of Emergency Management rediness initiatives, Southeastern cultural resource management policy and mediation/MOUs with Native American tribal governments throughout the Southwest. 

Dr. Knight's International interests have included the development and training for Hazardous Materials Management/Emergency Response and Heath and Safety Policy development in the US, Canada and, the Bahamas. Her studies abroad have taken her to Brazil, China, Thailand, Hong Kong and Singapore, enriching her appreciation for cultural diversity in the development of mediated solutions.

She is currently the CEO of Knightworks, LLC, a consulting firm primarily engaged in bringing new data acquisition/development techniques for emerging opportunities in engineering and healthcare.

headline: Accelerating Data & AI Development and Diversity | Executive Director, The South Big Data Innovation Hub | CEO, The Data Career Academy
summary:
Executive Strategist for Fortune 500 Companies, Federal and State Government Agencies, as well as Individuals around Data Science, Big Data, Digital Transformation, Public-Private Partnerships, Artificial Intelligence (AI), Internet of Things (IoT), Machine Learning, and Analytics. 

Book Author of: "Data Careers, Training, and Hiring" by SpringerPress

Bio
Dr. Renata Rawlings-Goss worked with the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy, under the Obama administration, to define national Big Data policies and priority goals within the NITRD inter-agency Big Data Senior Steering group. She co-led the writing team for the National Big Data Strategic Plan with partners from (NSF, NIH, DARPA, DOE, NSA, NIST, NOOA, NASA, USGS, NRO, DHS, DOD, EPA, HHS, AHRQ, NARA, etc). Additionally, Renata was competitively awarded to the first cohort of AAAS Big Data Policy Fellows supporting Congress and the federal government.  At the National Science Foundation (NSF), she was instrumental in the creation of the National Data Science Organizers group (NDSO.io) and the implementation of the NSF’s priority goal to increase the U.S. workforce in data science. 

Dr. Rawlings-Goss is currently the founding Executive Director of the South Big Data Innovation Hub, whose mission is to catalyze partnerships among universities, industry, and government around Big Data, Data Science, and the “Internet of Things”. She also serves as the Director of Industry Partnerships for the Georgia Tech Institute for Data Engineering and Science (IDEaS).

She is a biophysicist by training and pursuing continuing efforts to increase the participation of women and underrepresented minorities in STEAM (Science, Technology, Engineering, Art/Design, and Math). To that end, she serves as the President/ CEO of Good with Data, LLC which runs The Data Career Academy.

In 2017 she founded the World Environmental Conservancy, Inc. where she oversees the principal programs of the organization which include protection of environmentally sensitive forested areas in North and South American, environmental education, and global meteorology research focusing on the Antarctic, Amazon and Mata Atlantica Forests. She has extensive experience in research involving engineering and geophysics fluid mechanics as well as atmospheric boundary layers, turbulence, and their applications to complex terrain and continent-ocean interactions. Dr. Pires has applied her background and expertise to studies of wind and marine energy generation, aerospace meteorology, and micrometeorology at the Alcantara Launching Center in Brazil and as a visiting scientist at the Center for Climate Science of the Jet Propulsion Laboratory at NASA. She has participated in research development meetings sponsored by the National Science Foundation in Thailand, Laos, Vietnam, and Cambodia and has delivered academic presentations in Brazil, Portugal, Italy, USA, UK, Austria, Switzerland and Peru. She provides renewable energy consultative services through LBMP Advisors, LLC and is one of the research scientists of the National Institute of Science and Technology for Climate Change (INCT-MC), Brazil. She holds a PhD in Meteorology from the National Institute for Space Research (INPE), a master’s degree in the fluid mechanics area of mechanical engineering from the Catholic University of Minas Gerais, and a bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering from the Federal University of Sao Joao del Rei, all in Brazil. Her postdoctoral studies were conducted at the Laboratory for Environmental Physics at the Center for Atmospheric Biogeosciences of the University of Georgia, USA, and at the Hydro-environmental Research Centre of the School of Engineering at Cardiff University, UK.

headline: Founder & CEO/CTO at PorterLogic | SupplyTech Startup of the Year (x2) | S&DCE 2024 Pros to Know Award Winner
summary:
Hi, I’m Jonathan, but most people call me Porter. I’ve been a builder and creator since I was a kid. My love for Legos and Lincoln Logs eventually migrated to technology and companies. I built my first website at 15 and started my first company in high school.

I’m one of the rare Atlanta natives that’s still here, and I developed my obsession with supply chain and warehouses at Georgia Tech (ISyE 2015). After spending my early career working in supply chain software at firms like Manhattan Associates, I started what would be my third company in 2020 — PorterLogic.

PorterLogic is a composable supply chain tech stack built for mid-market manufacturers and value-add distributors. Our platform gives supply chain teams the systems they need to maintain their competitive advantage without being forced into a box by packaged solutions. Spreadsheets don’t scale, and custom systems are expensive and hard to maintain. PorterLogic brings unprecedented flexibility with lower TCO than traditional systems.

Being a founder and CEO is more than a 9-5 job, and you can usually find me working somewhere along the Atlanta beltline. Just look for the guy with a Mac and a PorterLogic sticker!

headline: Champion of Equity: Research Analyst and Analytical Strategist Shaping Policies to Bridge Socioeconomic Divides
summary:
Dr. Angelica Thompson is a research analyst and analytical strategist committed to fostering equity based on race/ethnicity, socioeconomic status, gender identity, and sexual orientation. She works side by side with decision-makers to define and implement strategies that are based on data analysis and modeling to solve a variety of organizational challenges. 

As Director of Evaluation at Per Scholas, Dr. Thompson analyzes data to convey key insights and research opportunities that support leadership in implementing actionable recommendations to meet organizational goals. In her work as CEO and Director of Research and Evaluation at Data Works, LLC, she aids community-based organizations and government agencies, training on the use of data collection tools to back data innovation and continuous improvement processes. She’s recognized for her ability to identify the best and most reasonable evaluation methods, data collection processes, and causal identification strategies—formulating and applying models, interpreting data, and presenting recommendations to drive meaningful change.

Earlier in her career, Dr. Thompson was a Senior Education Researcher for CSEdResearch.org, a Research Advisor for Shelby County Schools, and a Child and Adolescent Therapist at Lakeside Behavioral Health Systems. She has taught undergraduate and graduate courses at the Memphis College of Art, the University of Phoenix, the University of Memphis, and Christian Brothers University. Course instruction has spanned Introduction to and Essentials of Psychology, Lifespan Development, Learning Processes and Assessment, and Educational Psychology.

Dr. Thompson is the co-founder and co-host of the A Queer Understanding podcast, providing a safe space for members of the LGBTQIA+ community to come together to share stories, perspectives, and resources.  And she is a member of the board for Communities in Schools Memphis. 

Dr. Thompson holds a Ph.D. in Educational Psychology and an M.S. in Psychology from the University of Memphis. Dr. Thompson also holds a Lean Six Sigma Green Belt and is a member of the American Evaluators Association (AEA), the American Educational Research Association (AERA), Stand for Children, Women Impacting Public Policy (WIPP), and the U.S. Women’s Chamber of Commerce.

headline: Producer / Director - Video & New Media
summary:
In 2008 Tabari was presented the chance to work the grand opening of Tyler Perry Studios, and it turned out to be an awesome opportunity. After learning the amazing infrastructure at Tyler Perry Studios, Tabari started his own company Blue Lion Club Production. Must recently Tabari Produced the feature film “First Impression” Starring Lamaan Rucker, Lisa Arrindell Anderson, Kimberly Elise, David & Tamela Mann.  Tabari was voted Georgia’s Best Independent Filmmaker of 2013 by the Georgia Entertainment Gala.

Tabari then moved on to worked in production on the ABC Pilot titled The Returned. Most recently he has signed on as the Creative Director for Moguldom Studios. With tons of entertainment industry experience, Tabari is poised to be Media’s next BIG name.

CDR Bobby R. Jones, is from Fayetteville, Georgia and graduated from The Westminster Schools of Atlanta. After accepting an appointment to the United States Naval Academy, Annapolis, he was designated a Surface Warfare Officer upon commissioning in May 2001. He received his Master’s Degree in National Security and Strategic Studies with an African Studies Concentration from the United States Naval War College.

CDR Jones’ sea duty assignments have been Deck
Officer onboard USS Germantown (LSD 42) and USS
Harpers Ferry (LSD 49), Fire Control Officer onboard USS Normandy (CG 60), Weapons and Combat Systems Officer onboard USS Stethem (DDG 63), and Executive Officer USS Anzio (CG 68) and Coastal Riverine Squadron FOUR (CRS-4). While at sea, he participated in Operations Enduring Freedom, Noble Eagle, Inherent Resolve and the recovery of 10 detained American Sailors near Farsi Island.

Ashore, CDR Jones’ past assignments include Admissions Counselor at the United States Naval Academy, United Nations Peacekeeper for the United Nations Mission in Liberia, Wargames Planner for the Missile Defense Agency, and Executive Assistant to the Commander of Military Sealift Command.

He assumed duties as Commanding Officer, Maritime Expeditionary Security Squadron FOUR (MSRON-4) in May 2020. While in command, he deployed and also assumed duties as Commander, Task Group 56.7, where he led various missions in the Fifth Fleet Area of Responsibility, to include force protection of American assets and infrastructure, assisting in the Afghanistan Evacuation Mission and strategic cooperative engagements with key American allies.

CDR Jones is the recipient of various awards and citations to include the Defense Meritorious Service Medal, the Meritorious Service Medal, the Joint Commendation Medal and multiple Battle “E” Awards. He is the 2021 Navy recipient of the Blacks in Government Military Meritorious Service Award.

headline: Director, Chief AI Officer, MentorUp Life Lab & Clinic
summary:
Science & Healthspan
Mining the wealth of health science discoveries gets me up in the morning with anticipation. Healthspan is of particular interest. 

Collaberation at Scale
Today it seems my life is increasingly impacted by decentralized computation and our crowd-resourced world and the shared pull our generation feels towards significance over success. Crowd development, crowd design, and crowd fulfillment are redefining the concept of collaboration on an unprecedented scale. 

New Translational Healthcare Models
Healthcare is not exempt from these movements towards a new world of how we do business. Increasingly, over the last 15 years, my world has moved towards the expanding global markets of Asia, India, and China more recently. While COVID redefined our relationships with foreign markets and China in particular we still have a lot to gain from our understanding of and lessons from "them and us". The foundations of a 21 Century model for health care, inclusive of incorporating the edge of science and technology, offers enticing promise for new frontiers to address the long struggled-over areas of care reform, translational medicine, personalized treatment, cell health, immunology, healthier longer longevity, and care augmented by AI.

Team Playing
I value the synergy and personal satisfaction of working in a team environment that challenges individual performance and fosters an inspiring community. For this reason, I have come to place as much value on who people are and how we work well together than skills, experience, and industry equity. Opportunity and returns have become more about Who than What. We are drawn to demonstrations of performance excellence and expertise, yet for me, it is from collaborative partnerships and shared commitments where those flourish and offer the most reward. 

Team Rules
In an effort to build a rewarding life journey both professionally and in life generally, I have chosen to align with those who can share the following team operating principles:

•  Demonstrate gentleness, dignity, and respect     
•  Communicate with frankness, honesty, and clarity
•  Avoid blame and pettiness   
•  Keep agreements   
•  Assume good intentions   
•  Ask for help 
•  Seek mentors     
•  Take risks; learn from what doesn’t work     
•  Take ownership of outcomes
•  Attack problems, not people     
•  Innovate embracing science and technology frontiers  
•  Do it all with integrity, enthusiasm, and joy

headline: Exit Your Business on Your Terms Using Our Proprietary PowerExit™ Strategy | M&A Advisor | MBA Faculty at UGA | Founder, Brio Business Academy
summary:
You get the emails...right?

The ones with offers to buy your business. Your dopamine skyrockets when you see the numbers...

$5M...$10M...$100M...

These are what we call "prop" offers. 

Time and time again, we've seen owners succumb to the temptation of selling their business blindly based on these unsolicited offers...

Not knowing they give up most - if not all - control over the exit when they fly blind into these deals.

Business owners, we know exactly what you want: The right price for your business and a deal on your terms.

So you can exit WITHOUT any regret.

You crave control. It's been coded into your DNA since birth.

That's also why you became a business owner in the first place, right? To have total control and power over your time and income.

The only way you can get both is if you pull the 3 levers to any successful business exit:

➡️ Control over the transaction process
➡️ Developing a competitive market for your business
➡️ Identifying a broad scope of ideal buyers

Let me show how we've helped hundreds of business owners secure the right deal on their terms.

The PowerExit™ Strategy is our proprietary process to

1) Create confidential exposure by properly marketing the business sale for you to the right parties
2) Discover the true valuation of the business and implement systems to maximize the sale price

summary:
I've been in the media industry since 1999, starting as a  DJ at a small Gospel Station in Metro Atlanta. I started making money for my employer through NTR (non-traditional Revenue before it was the Buzz).  In 2011 I started BG AD Group as a marketing firm to help organizations improve their local advertising. Today it serves more than multiple companies across the Country. My background in the advertising industry is focused on Automotive, Education, and Events. 

IN 2019 we jumped into the PODCAST space and created the BG PODCAST network, Podcast is what we do. From production, creating, buying, development, and all things podcast. We help publishers, radio stations, DJs, brands, municipalities, schools, and influencers develop and win in the podcast world. We also help with media buys and placement. As of 5/13/22, we produce 25 plus podcasts a week on a variety of niche subjects. 

BG's primary Podcast focus is on Hyperlocal and regional brands, publishers, schools, municipalities, and subjects. We have developed new revenue sources for our partners, and continue to grow weekly. We use data, technology, and interest to create an award-winning podcast. In 2021 our first year in the News podcast space we were awarded a multimedia award from the Georgia Press Association. We have created a sports-based podcast with followings of over 200,000 monthly downloads, a Faith-based podcast like Southern Gospel News podcast that Feedspot.com says is the top Gospel Music podcast in the world.  In addition, we continue to expand into new markets and create branded-specific podcasts. 

We have presented at Conferences and conventions on the growth of podcasts, and podcast expos around the country including PODFEST, 2022 Newspaper Mega-Conference, and Georgia DOAS conference, and have been featured guests on Borrell and Associates podcast and interviewed by many other trade publications. We have been called the "King of Hyperlocal podcasting."

I am married, have two children, and split time between our homes in Cobb County and Fannin County Georgia.  I've been active in youth sports, fundraising, Rotary, faith-based organizations, and education.

headline: Business Coach
summary:
I am the CEO and Creative Director at Rock Paper Scissors. I joined the company in 2005 after graduating magna cum laude with a bachelor’s degree from Appalachian State University. My journey at RPS began with the role of Project Manager and I moved up the ranks very quickly. Prior to assuming the role of CEO and Creative Director, I held the role of Account Executive and Art Director. In my current position, I oversee the vision and direction of the company, as well as working with my team to develop brands that connect with our clients’ audiences and marketing solutions that help our clients grow their businesses.

I am also a certified EMyth Business Coach. Having gone through a year of coaching with the EMyth program myself, I know the value of having an individual outside of the company to discuss challenges and successes with and bounce ideas off of. The coaching I received helped RPS work through the challenges of the economic recession of the late 2000s, and I realized that I wanted to help others work through the challenges that business owners face, which lead me to become a coach with EMyth in 2013.

In addition to my commitment to RPS and our clients, I am actively involved in a number of professional and civic organizations such as the Gwinnett Chamber of Commerce, Leadership Gwinnett, Community Foundation for Northeast Georgia, Janus Institute, Gwinnett Coalition for Health and Human Services, Aurora Theatre, Barefoot in the Park Fine Art Festival, and Rotary Club of Lawrenceville, among others. Through these organizations, I enjoy helping other businesses grow and supporting the community in which I live and work.
position_description_1: Black Creek Coaching was founded to help business owners grow their businesses by focusing on the relationships internally with your team through your culture and externally with your customers through your marketing.
position_description_2:
In my role as CEO and Creative Director, I work with business and organizations that are at a crossroads and who need change. This can come from the desire to grow due to stagnation or shrinkage, or because your organization is ready to grow. 

In order to grow, most organizations need to change what they are currently doing and thinking. We know what it takes to help an organization to change. Change starts with asking hard questions to get to the core of who a business is and what it will take to really move the needle, and we are really good at asking the hard questions so that we can then create solutions to solve these problems with your branding and marketing efforts.

We create brands that reflect our clients and the hard work they put in that makes them so successful. Our business-based, creative strategy not only brings fresh ideas to the table, but also gives clients the opportunity to truly describe, and often discover who they are and how they want their brand to reflect that. 

We firmly believe that collaboration is one of the greatest components of a successful brand and growth strategy. We don't believe in having just clients, but instead creating partnerships. Truly understanding your organization’s anatomy [mission, vision, and values] allows us to fully invest and grow as a business partner. This means that your growing pains are our growing pains, we celebrate your victories like they’re our own, and we use all of those experiences to refine your marketing strategy moving forward.

Some of the more notable brands I have worked with include: CDC, Cabbage Patch Kids, Carry-On Trailer, Pigtails & Crewcuts, Discovery Point Childcare Centers, Swoozies, United Supply Company, Usher Foundation, Community Foundation for Northeast Georgia, Aurora Theatre, Janus Institute, Gateway85 Gwinnett CID, and City of Duluth to name a few.
position_description_3: As a former EMyth client, I know firsthand that building a successful business is a deliberate process. If you leave the growth and development of your business to chance, you might not be happy with—or even recognize—the resulting company. I enjoy giving my clients the perspective to objectively analyze the state of their company, the guidance to develop the structure needed to reach their goals, and the support to work through issues that stand in the way of their success.
position_description_4: Having literally grown up in the theatre, I pursued a degree in theatrical design with my specialization in both costume and scenery. Upon my graduation, I served as a design contractor for the Aurora Theatre including the costume design for the inaugural mainstage production in Lawrenceville of "Annie Get Your Gun". Favorite productions included "Last of the Red Hot Lovers", "A Year with Frog and Toad", "Damn Yankees", "Chicago", "Storytelling Ability of a Boy", "Boom", "Dinosaur: The Musical", and, of course, countless "Christmas Canteen" productions.
position_description_5: When I started my college experience, I only had interest in scenic design, but after a semester of study in the costume shop, picked up a new skill and passion for costuming. This included designing for both the mainstage and black box productions at Appalachian State University, as well as serving as an instructional assistant in the costume shop for three years helping other students learn the skills they needed. My roles included serving as a Stitcher, First Hand, Milliner, Designer and Instructional Assistant for the ASU Costume Shop.

summary: Stephen J. Alford is a thought leader, serial entrepreneur, investor, creative director, and communications expert with a proven track record of driving results and inspiring teams and leaders to reach their full potential. With a unique blend of strategic thinking, creative vision, and effective communication skills, Alford has achieved success in various industries, including education consulting, marketing promotions, high-yield investing, public relations management, and content development and distribution. Whether launching a new product, rebranding a company, creating narratives, managing a crisis, or leading a team, Stephen Alford delivers with an unwavering commitment to excellence.
position_description_1:
As the President and CEO of EDhear, Inc., Stephen Alford plays a pivotal role in elevating educational organizations across multiple levels. With his extensive expertise, Stephen has successfully guided K-12 organizations, colleges, nonprofits, and education partners in formulating and executing impactful business and communication strategies. He has been instrumental in helping various school districts and educational leaders not only meet but surpass their goals. This includes helping to secure millions in grants for student and community programs, achieving a 100% staffing success rate in challenging schools, and crafting messages and strategic communications that resonate deeply with all stakeholders.

Alford's impact extends to the digital arena, where he has overseen the complete redesign and launch of websites and mobile applications for schools and districts, enhancing their online presence and engagement. He has also developed comprehensive communications strategies and crisis management plans, including implementing strategic initiatives that address key educational challenges such as teacher compensation, recruitment, retention, and virtual learning. 

Stephen Alford is the executive producer of a host of education-focused television programs, further showcasing his commitment to advancing educational discourse. His work has profoundly impacted various aspects of education, including leadership transitions, student discipline, teacher recruitment/retention, and union relations. Alford's work has significantly strengthened community and parent engagement and enhanced the value of schools, school districts, and school leaders in their communities.
position_description_2: Stephen J. Alford is a creative leader with a unique ability to produce thought-provoking visual narratives that resonate with targeted audiences. For nearly a decade, Alford has created and produced a series of cable television programs, including Difference Makers, Beyond the Call, Prodigy, Leadership Matters, INtech, Perspectives, Road to Success, and Point of View.  In addition, he has written and produced award-winning campaign ads, public service announcements, and corporate training videos. In addition, Alford leads a team of talented post-production editors helping businesses enhance their instructional design projects.
position_description_3: In his tenure as Director of Think Feel Do, Inc., Stephen Alford expertly developed and implemented strategies and communication campaigns tailored for municipalities, businesses, business leaders, and community leaders. He successfully led numerous programs, including the Special Purpose Local Option Sales Tax (SPLOST) awareness campaign, a safer communities initiative, an airport concessions quality service program, and an airport development pitch. Known for his strategic insight, Stephen also served as a trusted advisor to elected officials, assisting them in adeptly managing public service's complex commitments and responsibilities. Additionally, he supported K-12 organizations and education leaders, helping them to lead successful teams and organizations. His work at Think Feel Do, Inc. underscored his commitment to driving impactful initiatives and achieving organizational success in a dynamic environment.
position_description_4:
As the Executive Director of Communications for Atlanta Public Schools, Stephen J. Alford led a team of communications professionals tasked with managing the organization's brand. His comprehensive management portfolio included overseeing the district’s radio, television, and cable television stations and all print and electronic publications, websites, parent notification systems, social media channels, district events, and media relations. Alford revitalized the school system’s cable channel by producing five new shows: "The Board Room," "APS News," "myAPS (Employee) News," "Perspectives," and "Difference Makers."

In addition to his media achievements, Alford successfully managed philanthropic, corporate, and community relationships with the school district, which resulted in a groundswell of support for the district's students and community stakeholders. He also implemented a strategic communications management system that allowed all schools and school district departments to codify and enhance their communications.

Furthermore, he developed and managed a comprehensive crisis communications strategy to address numerous district issues, including the aftermath of the infamous CRCT standardized test cheating scandal, abrupt leadership changes, school shootings, school closures, redistricting, and a gas leak at an elementary school, among other crises. His deep understanding of public, private, and post-secondary education enabled him to effectively craft messages that resonated with parents, community members, business partners, and taxpayers, demonstrating his adeptness in strategic communication within diverse educational settings.
organization_title_5: Director of Public Relations and Communications
position_description_5:
During his tenure as Director of Public Relations and Communications for Atlanta Public Schools (APS), Stephen J. Alford led a transformative era in which the district received numerous accolades, including state and national Superintendent of the Year, Board of Education of the Year, and Board Member of the Year. He spearheaded the redesign and successful launch of the school district's main website and over 100 school websites, significantly enhancing the digital presence and accessibility of APS.

Alford also played a critical role in managing the crisis communications and public relations efforts during the CRCT cheating scandal, which profoundly impacted the district. His strategic approach helped him navigate this challenging period effectively. Additionally, Stephen led the management of all digital communications for the school district, ensuring cohesive and timely dissemination of information to all stakeholders.

Alford was instrumental in planning and managing a variety of successful school district conferences and events, further demonstrating his comprehensive leadership in communication and public relations. Alford’s efforts were crucial in managing the communications process requirements that enabled APS to regain full accreditation. Stephen Alford consistently crafted and distributed messages that underscored the school system’s total customer value.
position_description_6:
As a Senior Technology Analyst for Atlanta Public Schools, Stephen Alford was integral in advancing educational technology initiatives. Working closely with the Director of Instructional Technology, Stephen helped implement numerous learning technology initiatives that enabled educators to integrate advanced technology into their classrooms. This included the deployment of vetted software applications, the rollout of 1-to-1 computer programs for students, and the training and usage of smartboards, significantly enhancing interactive learning opportunities.

Stephen also played a pivotal role in managing a train-the-trainer model, which expedited the delivery system for introducing new strategies in learning technology programs across school divisions and individual schools. This approach not only streamlined the implementation process but also ensured that educators were well-equipped to utilize new technologies effectively.

Additionally, Stephen served as an Atlanta Public Schools liaison for key school district partners, including prominent organizations like the Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation and the Annie E. Casey Foundation. In this capacity, he helped facilitate critical partnerships supporting various educational technology initiatives, further contributing to the district's mission of enhancing educational outcomes through technology integration.

headline: NeurotechforGood | Neuroethics Prof. turned Strategist | Connecting builders, decision-makers, and end users
summary:
Gap finder, bridge builder.

I’m inspired by ambitious tech innovation projects that aim to be ethically bold and globally impactful. Working at the frontiers of emerging tech, I use my PhD-training in neuroscience and ethics to lead strategic tech visioning that incorporates ethics design thinking to help align innovator values with societal interests. Dedicated to cross-sectoral dialogue, I’m frequently called upon as trusted advisor, collaborator, and convener of high-level global stakeholders across academia, industry, and government to create actionable recommendations and policy. As an internationally recognized speaker and commentator, I enjoy bringing insights and facilitating opportunities for shared discovery and co-creation of solutions for today’s (and tomorrow’s) thorniest ethical issues in tech. 

Bio: 
Dr. Karen S. Rommelfanger received her PhD in neuroscience and received postdoctoral training in neuroscience and neuroethics. Her research explores how evolving neuroscience and neurotechnologies challenge societal definitions of disease and medicine. Dr. Rommelfanger is an Associate Professor in the Departments of Neurology and Psychiatry and Behavioral Sciences, the Neuroethics Program Director at Emory University’s Center for Ethics, and Senior Associate Editor at the American Journal of Bioethics Neuroscience and on the first neuroethicist to be called to the editorial advisory board of Neuron. She is dedicated to cross-cultural work in neuroethics serving as ethicist to the China-India Mental Health Alliance and is co-chair of the Neuroethics Workgroup of the International Brain Initiative. She is an appointed member to the NIH BRAIN Initiative Neuroethics Working Group and ambassador to the EU Human Brain Project’s Ethics Advisory Board.  She also served as Neuroethics Subgroup member of the Advisory Committee to the Director at NIH for designing a roadmap for BRAIN 2025. She is a member of the World Economic Forum's Global Futures Council and of the Defense Advanced Research Agency's Neurotechnology ELSI Panel. A key part of her work is fostering communication across multiple stakeholders in neuroscience. Her commitment led to the founding of the world's first neuroethics strategy and consulting firm, Ningen Neuroethics Co-Lab. Facilitating community conversations, she is a frequent contributor and commentator in popular media such as The New York Times, NPR, and The Huffington Post.

Specialties: Neuroscience & Ethics, Tech innovation, Policy, Neurodiplomacy, Cross-cultural ethics, Participatory Governance

With that versatility, he has produced and directed just over 100 music videos, a dozen documentaries and network television specials for BET, TLC, Word Network and more; a handful of national TV commercials and his first movie won the New York International Film Festival spawning a national craze for Black College Marching Bands.

A musician since the 6th grade, Lassiter has played nearly every instrument in the brass family, specializing on the trumpet. As an editor and columnist for the Atlanta Daily World Newspaper, & Upscale Magazine, he covered & photographed every major event from the SUPER BOWL to the OLYMPICS, WORLD SERIES, GRAMMY AWARDS, NBA FINALS, All-Star games and more. His features have appeared across the nation.

Recently, he was given a proclamation from the mayor of his hometown, inducted into the National Black College Alumni Distinction Hall Of Fame, a Lifetime Achievement Literacy Classic Award and the coveted Stellar Award for “Video-Of-The Year”. He’s a voter for the Emmy and Grammy Awards.

Darryl says he gets a lot of inspiration from his wife Krystyn. They have two daughters and two sons.

headline: Co-Founder of Sought + Found
summary:
Throughout the years I have had a few careers, starting in 1984 with my entry into the world of IT after graduating from college.  I worked the first half of that career in the NASA/Department of Defense world and eventually made my way to the commercial side in the mid-1990s.  At one point I was the Director of Systems Engineering for a large-scale Air Force project and from there made my way into project and program management.

As my parents became elderly and handicapped, I took on more of an eldercare role for them as they made their respective ways through their final years.  In 2010 I decided to transition out of IT and into real estate in the Austin, Texas area.

It was in 2016 that a friend of mine and I decided to join forces to start up Sought + Found.  With the growth of that business came an additional opportunity to help clients not only with the home they were selling, but also the new home they purchased.  My business partner and I decided to startup a new business in 2018 to address those projects and we called it Designing Your View.  We also decided it was best to bring on a full-time interior designer to handle the incoming and ongoing clients.

We became authorized dealers for both the Hunter Douglas and Graber product lines so that we could offer clients the best options in the industry for window coverings.  And with the changes in how/where people work due to the pandemic, our interior designer is able to help clients anywhere in the continental United States with virtual consultations for window coverings.

headline: Author, Professional Writer/Scriptwriter, Business Owner, Editor-in-Chief, Filmmaker, Business Consultant, Accountant, Former Media Personality, Public Speaker
summary:
Meet Boss Lady Mae, the extraordinary Wordsmith, Author, Public Speaker, Filmmaker, and Business Consultant. Boss Lady Mae has established herself as an electrifying force, brimming with dynamic talents and remarkable accomplishments within the industry.
 
For over 26 years, Boss Lady Mae has showcased her writing prowess, serving as a highly sought-after ghostwriter for books, TV/movie scripts, stage plays, documentaries, and commercials. Her exceptional skills have earned her the status of a best-selling author, with eight books bearing her name and over 165 eBooks as a ghostwriter. She has also penned six screenplays, ten stage plays, four documentaries, six TV shows, and hundreds of articles, captivating audiences with her ability to weave compelling stories.
 
Not only a master of words, Boss Lady Mae is the Founder/Executive Director of Boss Ladies on the Move (now rebranded as Women Leaders Network), a groundbreaking organization dedicated to empowering forward-thinking women. Her advocacy for women's success and empowerment is unwavering, and she continues to impact this area significantly.

As a public speaker with 24 years of experience, Boss Lady Mae has graced the stages, captivating audiences with her insightful workshops, seminars, trade shows, and webinars. Renowned for her expertise in professional development, marketing, women's issues, and media and entertainment, she has become a highly sought-after speaker. Her reputation as an expert is further solidified by her membership with WMC SheSource and a profile on the All-American Speakers website, showcasing the best talent in the industry.
 
Boss Lady Mae's creative endeavors have garnered substantial recognition throughout her career. Her books, including "The Boss Ladies, Book 1," "The Boss Ladies, Book II," "A Modern Day Jezebel Saved by Grace," "Give A Man A Fish," "Amber Alert," and "Same Ole, Same Ole" have achieved best-seller status, while her stage plays and screenplays have received critical acclaim. As she continues to write, direct, and inspire, Boss Lady Mae's journey is only just beginning. With the recent release of "The Enchanting Tales of Marley, Carley, and Zahara" and the upcoming releases of "The Boss Ladies, Book III," "Single Ladies Wait on Your Boaz," "The Devine Truth about Nero's Spirit is Alive in America's Era of Discord," and "The Tales and Journey of Mississippi Po'Boy," she captivates audiences across various genres.

headline: Helping people and brands tell stories that move | Director, Cinematographer | Founder, Studio IX | Advocate for moms in film
summary:
As a documentary filmmaker and cinematographer, I specialize in short form storytelling with a focus on social justice and equality and I am dedicated to fighting for a more inclusive future of storytellers and stories told. Through my work I’ve filmed the Special Olympics World Games in Abu Dhabi, embedded in protests on the streets of Johannesburg, followed a single mother to work on a potato farm in Romania, documented LeBron James playing around with his sons before winning his third NBA MVP award, investigated workers rights on a shipyard in Alabama, and everything in between. 

As the Founder and President of Studio IX, a nonprofit organization working to level the playing field for womxn in film, I work to provide emerging filmmakers with the resources, confidence and funding needed to create a documentary short film used to help break into the industry and sustain a career. 

Prior to launching Studio IX, I was the Director of Glassbreaker Films an initiative funded by The Helen Gurley Brown Foundation dedicated to finding and funding women directors in nonfiction film. During my time with Glassbreaker Films, including a partnership with The Center for Investigative Reporting, I oversaw the production of over 30 short films and several digital series. My team was nominated for a National News and Documentary Emmy Award, won an  Edward R. Murrow Award and a Gracie Award; published on platforms such as Netflix, NYT Op Docs and PBS; and premiered at festivals around the world, including Sundance, SXSW, Hotdocs and Tribeca.

Before transitioning to documentary full time, I was an on-camera anchor for Sports Illustrated’s breaking news video team, SI Wire, and I worked as a video producer for the Miami Heat, covering back-to-back NBA championships. And once upon a time, before a back injury ended my career, I was a professional soccer player-- a two-sport Division I varsity athlete at Penn State, a two-time NSCAA Academic All American, and a five-time Big Ten Conference Champion.

headline: Partner at LFE Capital
summary:
I’ve been pushing limits and blazing trails since I became a chemical engineer 30 years ago. My passion for science is rooted in discovery, making my transition to business development a natural progression.

From engineering patented innovation to spearheading acquisitions to imagining opportunities in new markets, I have a proven track record for business incubation and long-term growth. This includes conceptualizing and building what is now Lubrizol Life Science, a thriving Lubrizol business innovating chemistry for fast-growing beauty, home and healthcare applications.The incubation and growth of Lubrizol Life Science required strategy development, organizationaldesign, global immersion in healththcare markets and several large pharmaceutical and medical device acquisitions. This enabled Lubrizol to invent novel patient-focused products and services, affecting the lives of billions of people.

In my current role as Senior Vice President of Lubrizol Corporate Ventures, I challenge an inspired team as we lean into Lubrizol’s 90 years of chemistry expertise to develop, formulate, test and commercialize breakthroughs, turning challenges into opportunities for our partners. My team of seasoned scientists, engineers and business leaders work in partnership with our customers to facilitate innovations in emerging, high-impact industries, driving the hydrogen, electric, and energy ecosystem.

Novel technology energizes me, and I’m so proud to have been recognized with the R&D 100 award and the NorTech Innovation award for pioneering commercial products. I feel strongly that transforming the world should not come at the cost of the planet. That’s why I’m pleased that so much of our work is rooted in sustainability with opportunities to help the world Move Cleaner, Create Smarter and Live Better.

Forward thinking mentors – both men and women – have supported me throughout my career as a chemical engineer and as a business leader. I’m fortunate that this has included on-the-job mentorship, as well as education by leaders as part of Wharton’s executive training. headline: Chairman and Shareholder at Oro Advisors
summary:
Jiorjio Fetterman is the founder and Managing Member of Oro Advisors, LLC. Oro provides co-sourced C-suite support for investment advisors.

Jiorjio was previously at Clearlake Capital from 2017 to 2019 serving as Vice President of Finance and Operations. Prior to Clearlake, Jiorjio was the Assistant Controller at Canyon Partners from 2008 to 2017 where he was responsible for back-office accounting and operations. Prior to Canyon, Jiorjio was a Senior Auditor at Deloitte where he worked on financial statement audits of investment funds and mortgage companies.

During his decades in the investment management industry Jiorjio managed funds that invested globally with a variety of hedge fund and private equity strategies and instruments including real-estate, REITS, public equities, distressed debt, bonds, mortgage-backed securities, trade claims, bank debt, structured products, private equity, futures, options, derivatives, commodities and foreign exchange.

Jiorjio has been active in shaping best practices in the alternative asset industry. He is frequently invited to participate in industry conferences as a moderator, panelist and speaker and is often quoted in industry publications. He has written and presented on a wide range of hedge fund operational and business topics.

Jiorjio has been a Certified Public Accountant (CPA) since 2007.

headline: Founder and CEO at Christian Business Incubator
summary: I am the Founder and CEO of eStore Incubator, a one-on-one coaching program that has helped hundreds of “regular people” from around the globe launch six-figure ecommerce businesses from scratch.
position_description_1:
Hi, my name is Paul, and my team and I help Christians start their first or next business using my predictable Simple Business Machine systems and Escape the "40-40" Rat Race.

I've run a Christian Virtual Business Incubator for fifteen years, worked with more than eight hundred sixty-five clients, and started ten companies in ten different markets with ten different business models.

The first two were train wrecks, the next three were six figures, and the last three seven, and I can share a few ideas I've found valuable.

The 40-40 Plan (40 hours/40 years), is that God's best for our lives? 
Is that all there is?

"And you shall remember the Lord your God, for it is He who gives you power to get wealth, that He may establish His covenant which He swore to your fathers, as it is this day." Deuteronomy 8:18.

According to this verse and many others, we don’t believe the "40-40" plan is all there is for Christians who actually believe. 

And since God is love, that means that His covenant is a love covenant. 

In the Kingdom, we are taught to love people and use money. 

After all, it's money that funds ministries, builds hospitals, feeds children, and rescues the trafficked.

More money = more good.

In the world's system, it's the opposite; we are taught to love money and use people. 

We believe in the biblical principle of earning our financial and time independence, with God's power, by building simple virtual business machines that can eventually operate 100% without us.

We do this by building simple, predictable, and dependable "Service First" businesses based on uncompromising and unapologetic Christian Biblical principles. 

We need a Mentor, a Business Model, and a bulletproof Mindset.

If you're interested in starting your first or next business with predictability, simplicity, and profitability, based on God's biblical principles, click here to learn more: https://christianentrepreneurinc.com/tips?utm=linkedin

I learned:
How to build business systems run by excellent people.

How to chase my wife around the house.

headline: Interim Executive Director at Austin Technology Incubator
summary:
I create or join leadership teams to take on bold, creative changes and cultivate growth opportunities in radical ways.  And do it with humility and humor.

If you are looking for leadership that helps move your organization forward, let's talk.  My experience would be of interest to you. I have a long history of inciting change with large, multi-national corporations, the State Department in Washington DC, and successful entrepreneurial startups in the technology and public service arenas. 

With my experiences and my network of connections, I know how to drive results. 

In my experiences, I’ve motivated some of the top people in their field, from science and technology to public policy and community building, to achieve new and innovative pursuits. We all win when we strive to grow beyond our current area of expertise. 

You’ll see from my profile that I built a track record of success with many organizations in a variety of circles. I can bring my network to you to cultivate new possibilities in areas you may never have before considered. My profile includes non-profit leadership, board service, government service and senior leadership in a corporate structure. I bring a business perspective that focuses on what direction should be taken and why those decisions should be made. 

I’ve led organizations in developing their technological programs to keep pace with the industry standards and best practices. I know that if you’re not planning for tomorrow’s advances, you’re planning to fall behind. 

Currently I am considering opportunities in the Austin, Texas area where I can utilize my talents to bring about positive change in an organization that is open to bold, new ideas and approaches to their business model. This organization could be a corporation, a non-profit, or a government entity. The one constant I seek is the willingness to grow.  Faster. 

If this sounds like you, please message me here on LinkedIn. 

It will be fun.

1. TexasSnacks.com - We're the first and world's largest unofficial re-seller of Buc-ee's products.

2. MiningSyndicate.com - We sell hardware, services and software related to crypto mining.

3. FastTreeCare.com - DFW-based tree trimming company that we incubated from scratch with an operating partner in the summer of 2023. We are rapidly expanding and having a ton of fun.

4. Voltera - Healthcare AI startup that helps skilled nursing facilities save 5-6 figures per year.

5. RV/MH Parks - We own an RV park in Waco, TX and I am a GP on a large RV park in Louisiana as well.

6. cofounders.com - This is the holdco for most of everything above. We fund undergrads and provide them with a salary, training and a business idea to launch alongside us. It's a lot of fun.

7. Content - I write ~40,000 words of free, longform business content every month between X, LinkedIn and to 7,000+ newsletter subscribers. This content is read by 20-30 million people every month and is perfect for fellow business nerds.

8. Other - I am always tinkering with and/or incubating a few other stealth ideas at any given time.

I have a deep passion for entrepreneurship, writing and real estate. My writing attempts to put all 3 together.

I live in DFW on a few acres with a beautiful wife of 16 years and 4 kids ages 7-13.

A few more unique things about me:

- My wife and I each donated a kidney to a stranger so say thanks to the boy who donated his lungs to my daughter. I'm deeply passionate about altruistic kidney donation.

- I saw all 50 states in 60 days with my family in an RV

- After being obese for my 20s, I lost it all and ran 15 ultramarathons and hold records in several of them

- I partnered with the legendary John McAfee on a crypto project in 2018

- After being rejected by Buc-ee's to be the first to sell their products online, I went ahead and did it anyway, with my good friend and cousin Kirk Salisbury. That is now a thriving 7 figure company.

- I have started over 20 companies and absolutely freaking love what I do. Business is my hobby, profession and passion, and it doesn't feel like work.

Thanks for following along. For a deeper look into my work and writings please join my free weekly newsletter here: https://bit.ly/42zpARg

headline: MSBA Student at UMass Amherst || Ex-Zomato || SRCC'21
summary:

Building upon my Bachelor's in Commerce from Shri Ram College of Commerce, I honed my analytical skills during my 2.5 year tenure at Zomato, a leading online food delivery platform. My experience at Zomato instilled in me a strong desire to explore the depths of data analytics further, fueling my pursuit of a career where I can continue to uncover actionable insights and drive meaningful change. 

I am excited about the prospect of applying my skills and knowledge to make a tangible impact in the field of business analytics, driving innovation and growth in dynamic industries. Let's connect and explore opportunities to collaborate on exciting data-driven ventures.

headline: IT Program and Project Manager and IT Consultancy Services, Founder, Locum Integration, LLC
summary:
A Technologist's Philosophy from a Contrarian Thinker: Building the Future, One Project at a Time:

For the past 25 years, I've been immersed in the ever-evolving landscape of technology. I’ve been in the field; I know what it’s like. I did not become a PM by reading a book - I got my hands dirty – a LOT.

I’ve done it all, from SCADA networks to microwave shots. From defense and government to energy, utilities, and telecommunications, I witnessed firsthand the transformative power of IT and the web, launching a start-up back in the Dotcom days. This furthered a deep interest in pursuing entrepreneurial routes, finding and exploring new ways of creating market efficiencies, across all industry verticals.

Technology isn't just my business; I describe it as a constant wellspring of thorny curiosity. Just when I think the value-add of technology has diminished, something new comes out which makes me think, “OK, maybe we can go a bit further.” Right now, the possibilities of micro-nuclear reactors, Robotics, AI and machine learning hold particular interest for me. 

In addition, we’re still figuring out ways and building models for identifying highly skilled talent in this current, rather difficult marketplace. This child of inspiration and angst is my LLC, Locum Integration LLC, which has been in operation since 2013. 

This idea for “doing” the market differently commenced with our Locum “On-Demand PMO” model which we trademarked in 2016. It allows companies to spin up and utilize IT-PMO services as needed, on the fly, without recruiters or needing to put a person in a seat full-time. This well documented, well protected model often has me feeling like Michael Burry in “The Big Short” – lol - but I’m not wrong. (More on this later as the rest of the world catches up to the inevitability).

To give myself a voice and a platform, I've even built a state-of-the-art 4-camera, 4K digital media studio at home, a testament to my ongoing exploration. You should see this thing!

Whether you're tackling groundbreaking projects in AI, defense, government or energy, or seeking operational efficiencies in the hospitality sector, I'd love to connect and kick ideas around! 

I’m focused only on Corp-to-Corp opportunities and entrepreneurial activities at this time. Not interested in any W2 situations. I believe in the power of collaboration to push the boundaries of what's possible.

Let's chat! Reach out to me at locumintegration@gmail.com

JP

Cisco (NASDAQ: CSCO) enables people to make powerful connections--whether in business, education, philanthropy, or creativity. Cisco hardware, software, and service offerings are used to create the Internet solutions that make networks possible--providing easy access to information anywhere, at any time. 

Cisco was founded in 1984 by a small group of computer scientists from Stanford University. Since the company's inception, Cisco engineers have been leaders in the development of Internet Protocol (IP)-based networking technologies. Today, with more than 71,000 employees worldwide, this tradition of innovation continues with industry-leading products and solutions in the company's core development areas of routing and switching, as well as in advanced technologies such as home networking, IP telephony, optical networking, security, storage area networking, and wireless technology. In addition to its products, Cisco provides a broad range of service offerings, including technical support and advanced services. 

Cisco sells its products and services, both directly through its own sales force as well as through its channel partners, to large enterprises, commercial businesses, service providers, and consumers.

Amazon is guided by four principles: customer obsession rather than competitor focus, passion for invention, commitment to operational excellence, and long-term thinking. We are driven by the excitement of building technologies, inventing products, and providing services that change lives. headline: Director at Nyassa Retail Pvt
summary:
I walked away from a corporate career and decided to strike out on my own by making soaps. A first time entrepreneur, clueless but passionate, I let go of my 8 years of financial services experience. Nyassa was started in end of 2006

Nyassa was my modest but passionate attempt to create handmade soaps with ingredients that are absolutely nature-made. The encouragement  from our customers  has made us progress from a recognizable soap maker to a desirable bath & body products brand today.
 
Over the next few months, you will see a whole new range of Nyassa products that not only reflect our continued commitment to bring you  products of unmatched luxury and exceptional value, but  also demonstrate a refreshing philosophy shaped by our deeper understanding of our customers needs, likes, and wants.  We call this thinking ‘From Heaven and Earth’. Imagine the most exotic and mesmerizing of fragrances, exquisite and indelible, romantic and dreamy; Imagine a whole basket of pure and wholesome natural ingredients, from the bosom of the earth, beneficial to your skin and body; Now imagine them coming together harmoniously, elegantly, almost divinely, in a bath soap, or a body butter,or a handwash, or a face cream.
This is Nyassa. The best of heavenly fragrances together with the best of earthly ingredients. The coming together of two worlds creating an exciting new one. 
 
Everytime you pick up a Nyassa, you know everything about it. Like it is 100% vegetarian,we use no preservatives,no SLES or SLS in our products & are against animal testing.

6 yrs is not a long time,but we have come a long way.And we feel closer to nature than ever before. In the coming days, we will scour the earth and sweep the heavens to bring you the best of fragrances and the best of ingredients.That’s my promise.

Would like to connect with individuals with passion for natural products; 4-5 star hotels, boutique hotels, spas, salons for room amenities & bulk products; sme's & corporates for gifting

headline: CEO at Ripple Animation & Ripple Media
summary:
Madhura co-founded, Ripple Animation in 2014 to create explainer videos, product demo videos and other videos for business purposes. Ripple Animation is now a clear leader in the 'explainer video for business' space working with marquee clients like Amazon, E&Y, HDFC Bank, ICICI Lombard, Vodafone, Zycus and even the government. 

Ripple Animation's expertise lies in creating video content that meets business objectives and drives growth. The goal for most of Ripple Animation's clients is to engage with and convert customers at various points in the sales funnel. All processes at Ripple Animation are geared towards making sure that clients get videos that work for them, are delivered on time and are within budget.

Prior to starting Ripple Animation, Madhura ran Sharp Shooter Films (a TV commercial production company) which was a Joint Venture with the WPP group. 

Madhura is an investment banker by training. She worked on Wall Street in New York prior to moving back to India. 

Madhura is also an active angel investor with 45+ investments in India to date including 2 that have achieved unicorn status. 

She has received her BA in Economics from Lawrence University in Wisconsin.  She credits her Liberal Arts education for teaching her how to think through and solve business problems creatively.
